descriptions.description:
This screen shows a web browser displaying the p5.js Web Editor with JavaScript code on the left and a black canvas output area on the right. The UI shows several open tabs in Chrome, including "editor.p5js.org" and various other web pages.

**Code (JavaScript):**
```javascript
// Cities JSON
// https://gist.github.com/Miserlou/c5cd8364bf9b2420bb29

let cities;
let minLat = 90;
let maxLat = -90;
let minLong = 180;
let maxLong = -180;

function preload() {
  loadJSON("assets/cities.json", onLoad, onError);
}

function setup() {
  createCanvas(500, 400);
  console.log({cities});

for (let city of cities) {
  if (city.latitude < minLat) {
    minLat = city.latitude;
  }
  if (city.latitude > maxLat) {
    maxLat = city.latitude;
  }
  if (city.longitude < minLong) {
    minLong = city.longitude;
  }
  if (city.longitude > maxLong) {
    maxLong = city.longitude;
  }
```

**Visual output:**
The canvas is a black rectangle containing numerous small, scattered red dots that appear to form the shape of a geographic landmass (resembling North America).

